JOHANNESBURG - South Africa remains coronavirus free. The government says it plans to keep things that way. An emergency operation centre to deal with the outbreak has been set up. WATCH: Coronavirus: SA on high alert According to Health Minister Zweli Mkhize, the activation of the emergency centre means there are dedicated staff working on the coronavirus. Mkize says more staff will be added as discussions are taking place with relevant stakeholders and provinces. The virus has been spreading at rapid rates not just in China but in several other countries as well. WATCH: Health Minister gives update on coronavirus Over 200 people have already been declared dead in China and just this afternoon, Botswana confirmed it's first suspected coronavirus case. Watch the video above for more